HEADWORD: Sea heath
<hw>Sea" heath`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A low
perennial plant (<spn>Frankenia laevis</spn>) resembling heath, growing
along the seashore in Europe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

